{{Infobox person |image = |imagesize = | name = Christopher Townsend | birth_name = | other_names = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = [[visual effects supervisor]] | yearsactive = 1995-present | spouse = | children = }}
'''Christopher Townsend''' is a [[visual effects supervisor]]. He has worked in the visual effects industry for over 20 years. For over a decade, he was an artist and supervisor at [[Industrial Light and Magic]], and in 2007 became a freelance visual effects supervisor. He worked on ''[[Journey to the Center of the Earth (2008 Hollywood film)|Journey to the Center of the Earth]]'', the first ever stereoscopic motion picture shot and released digitally, ''[[The Wolverine (film)|The Wolverine]]'', ''[[Ninja Assassin]]'', ''[[Percy Jackson and the Olympians: The Lightning Thief]]'' and ''[[Captain America: The First Avenger]]''. He was nominated for a [[BAFTA]] and an [[Academy Award for Best Visual Effects]] for his work on ''[[Iron Man 3]]'',<ref name="Oscars2013">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oscars.org/awards/academyawards/legacy/ceremony/86th-winners.html |title=The 86th Academy Awards (2013) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=August 30, 2014 |work=Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences |publisher=AMPAS |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141001025332/http://www.oscars.org/awards/academyawards/legacy/ceremony/86th-winners.html |archivedate=October 1, 2014 |df= }}</ref> oversaw nearly 3000 shots on ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]'' and was the overall supervisor for ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2]]''. In 2015 he was given an Honorary [[Doctor of Arts]] degree by his alma mater, [[Coventry University]].
