'''Fillemon Elifas Shuumbwa''' affectionately known as Fillemon Shuumbwa yElifas lyaShindondola (born October. 10, 1932 - died by gun shot 16 August 1975 at [[Onamagongwa]]), Ondangwa area, Namibia) was the chief of [[Ondonga]] and chief minister of Ovamboland (1972–75).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newera.com.na/2017/04/21/ondonga-royal-squabbles-betrayal-or-autocracy/|title=Ondonga royal squabbles: Betrayal or autocracy?|first=New Era Staff|last=Reporter|date=21 April 2017|publisher=}}</ref> The [[Ondonga]] tribal area is situated around [[Namutoni]] on the eastern edge of [[Etosha pan]] in today's northern [[Namibia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.namibian.com.na/index.php?id=140981&page=archive-read|title=The royal fight for the Ondonga kingdom|publisher=}}</ref>

