'''Robert Xowie''' (born in the Wetr district of [[Lifou]] on August 27, 1962) is a [[New Caledonia]]n politician and pro-independence advocate. A [[Kanak people|Kanak]] of the Siloam tribe, Xowie served as President of [[Loyalty Islands Province]]<ref>{{cite book|title=Far East and Australasia 2003|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=e5Az1lGCJwQC|accessdate=26 September 2011|edition=34|year=2002|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=978-1-85743-133-9}}</ref> from 1999 until 2004, as well as [[mayor]] of [[Lifou]] from 1995 until 2001.
